But Charlie Dixon's return is the headline for Port, a big inclusion in more ways than one. GWS have dropped Xavier O'Halloran from the 22 for the returning Stephen Coniglio, which was a pretty straight up and down call for the Giants. Subs tonight are the two omitted players — Finlayson for Port and O'Halloran for GWS. No Nick Haynes tonight for the Giants.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Some sad news this afternoon with word that Ron Barassi, a true legend of our game in every sense, has died at the age of 87. Barassi's family confirmed Ron died today "due to complications from a fall". You can get the full story below. Barassi was a star during the Melbourne Football Club's glory years, helping them to six premierships between 1957 and 1963. A tall, fearless player, he pioneered the position of ruck rover. In 1964, Barassi moved to the Carlton Football Club and won two premierships. From Carlton he went to North Melbourne and won another two premierships with his tough coaching style.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Vale Ron Barassi

featuredLink.title: Ron Barassi, AFL legend and premiership player and coach, dies aged 87

children.content: Some sad news this afternoon with word that Ron Barassi, a true legend of our game in every sense, has died at the age of 87.
Barassi's family confirmed Ron died today "due to complications from a fall".
You can get the full story below.
Barassi was a star during the Melbourne Football Club's glory years, helping them to six premierships between 1957 and 1963.
A tall, fearless player, he pioneered the position of ruck rover.
In 1964, Barassi moved to the Carlton Football Club and won two premierships.
From Carlton he went to North Melbourne and won another two premierships with his tough coaching style.
